                    <msContents>
                        <summary><title type="uniform">Guðmundar saga biskups</title>. The saga of
                            this manuscript (the so-called oldest saga) is a compilation of
                                'Prestssaga', 'Hrafns saga', 'Íslendinga saga', 'Arons saga' and annals. AM 399 4to was one of
                            the manuscripts <name type="person" key="PedRes001">Peder Resen</name>
                            presented to the University Library in Copenhagen. This manuscript is
                            one of the few to have survived from this library, which was consumed in
                            the flames of the Great Fire of <name type="place" key="Copen01"
                                >Copenhagen</name> in <date when="1728">1728</date> as <name type="person"
                                key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> had borrowed it.</summary>
